RIFTSMUD DOMAIN WIZARD HANDBOOK

WHO THIS IS FOR
The backbone staff role. Domain wizards coordinate world areas, assign
work to Coding and Roleplay wizards, and manage who builds where.

POSITION AND ROLE
  position: domain_wiz
  wiz_role: domain (synced automatically from position)

TOOLS YOU MUST HOLD
  Staff of Dominion (command: dominate)
Granted on promotion. You cannot use dominate without this staff.

COMMAND ACCESS
Domain wizards do NOT get the broad creator or admin command paths.
You CAN use:
  Ambassador file tools: ed, cat, ls, cd, more, goto (file navigation)
  workroom
  dominate (via staff of dominion only)
If you hold an RP skill tool, you may also use tool/rptool for oversight
(domain oversight is allowed by the tool gate).

You CANNOT use by default:
  update, eval, dest, build/QCS, promote, demote, rid, warmboot

DOMINION STAFF MENU (dominate)
  1. Create new domain directory (/domains/<name>/rooms, monsters, obj)
  2. Assign domain to coding wizard (logged)
  3. List all domains
  4. Set domain description
  5. Teleport to domain start room
  6. Grant building access to player (logged)
  7. Revoke building access (logged)
  8. List players in domain
  9. Reset all loaded rooms in domain

DIRECTORY ACCESS
On promotion you receive:
  /realms/<yourname>/workroom.c
  /realms/<yourname>/area/ (room, npc, weap, armor subdirs)
  /domains/wizards/<yourname>/workroom.c (legacy path, optional)

Game world areas live under /domains/<areaname>/ (e.g. /domains/Praxis/).
Coding wizards usually build in /realms/<name>/area/ unless you assign
a shared domain path.

IMPORTANT: Options 6 and 7 log the grant but may still need an admin
to update /realms/ or /domains/ adm/access.c for full write access.
Contact an admin after granting access.

YOUR RESPONSIBILITIES
  Create and organize domain directories for Rifts content
  Assign coding tasks and directories to Coding wizards
  Coordinate RP wizards on skill fairness and player support
  Reset or inspect areas under your domains
  Keep Praxis and assigned world areas coherent

NOT YOUR JOB
  Promoting or demoting staff (Admin only)
  Running QCS or build commands without a staff of creation
  Wiping player files or shutting down the MUD
  Editing /secure/ or /std/ without admin approval

SEE ALSO
